{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Mat|4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","chapter":4,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":1,"text":"Then Jesus was led up by the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted by the devil.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":2,"text":"After he had fasted forty days and forty nights, he was hungry.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":3,"text":"Then the tempter approached him and said, “If you are the Son of God, tell these stones to become bread.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":4,"text":"He answered, “It is written: Man must not live on bread alone but on every word that comes from the mouth of God.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":5,"text":"Then the devil took him to the holy city, had him stand on the pinnacle of the temple,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":6,"text":"and said to him, “If you are the Son of God, throw yourself down. For it is written:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":7,"text":"Jesus told him, “It is also written: Do not test the Lord your God.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":8,"text":"Again, the devil took him to a very high mountain and showed him all the kingdoms of the world and their splendor.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":9,"text":"And he said to him, “I will give you all these things if you will fall down and worship me.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":10,"text":"Then Jesus told him, “Go away, Satan! For it is written: Worship the Lord your God, and serve only him.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":11,"text":"Then the devil left him, and angels came and began to serve him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":12,"text":"When he heard that John had been arrested, he withdrew into Galilee.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":13,"text":"He left Nazareth and went to live in Capernaum by the sea, in the region of Zebulun and Naphtali.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":14,"text":"This was to fulfill what was spoken through the prophet Isaiah:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":15,"text":"Land of Zebulun and land of Naphtali,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":16,"text":"The people who live in darkness","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":17,"text":"From then on Jesus began to preach, “Repent, because the kingdom of heaven has come near.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":18,"text":"As he was walking along the Sea of Galilee, he saw two brothers, Simon (who is called Peter), and his brother Andrew. They were casting a net into the sea —for they were fishermen.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":19,"text":"“Follow me,” he told them, “and I will make you fish for people.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":20,"text":"Immediately they left their nets and followed him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":21,"text":"Going on from there, he saw two other brothers, James the son of Zebedee, and his brother John. They were in a boat with Zebedee their father, preparing their nets, and he called them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":22,"text":"Immediately they left the boat and their father and followed him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":23,"text":"Now Jesus began to go all over Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, preaching the good news of the kingdom, and healing every disease and sickness among the people.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":24,"text":"Then the news about him spread throughout Syria. So they brought to him all those who were afflicted, those suffering from various diseases and intense pains, the demon-possessed, the epileptics, and the paralytics. And he healed them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":4,"verse":25,"text":"Large crowds followed him from Galilee, the Decapolis, Jerusalem, Judea, and beyond the Jordan.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","chapter":4,"paragraphStarts":[1,4,5,7,8,10,11,12,15,16,17,18,21,23],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Temptation of Jesus"},{"beforeVerse":12,"text":"Ministry in Galilee"},{"beforeVerse":18,"text":"The First Disciples"},{"beforeVerse":23,"text":"Teaching, Preaching, and Healing"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:4:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 1:12–13","book":"Mrk","chapter":1,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 4:1–13","book":"Luk","chapter":4,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Jesus was led up by the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted by the devil. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 15:61","book":"Jos","chapter":15,"verse":61,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 1:16","book":"Jdg","chapter":1,"verse":16,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 1:6–7","book":"Jhn","chapter":1,"verse":6,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 1:14